<figure class="aligncenter size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2025/12/Dan-Reed-care-team-16x9-1-1024x576.jpg" alt="Dressed as Santa, kidney transplant recipient Dan Reed returned&nbsp;to Mayo Clinic to thank his transplant team and spread holiday cheer.&nbsp;" class="wp-image-409196" srcset="https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2025/12/Dan-Reed-care-team-16x9-1-1024x576.jpg 1024w, https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2025/12/Dan-Reed-care-team-16x9-1-300x169.jpg 300w, https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2025/12/Dan-Reed-care-team-16x9-1-768x432.jpg 768w, https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2025/12/Dan-Reed-care-team-16x9-1.jpg 1026w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure>



<p><strong>Dressed as Santa, kidney transplant recipient Dan Reed returned&nbsp;to Mayo Clinic to thank his transplant team and spread holiday cheer.</strong>&nbsp;</p>



<p>"I knew 2025 would be a big year for me,"&nbsp;Dan&nbsp;says.&nbsp;</p>



<p>For Dan,&nbsp;May&nbsp;2025&nbsp;brought&nbsp;the greatest gift&nbsp;of all:&nbsp;the gift of life.&nbsp;</p>



<p>Dan's journey to transplant first&nbsp;came to light&nbsp;in 2024, when he shared his story publicly while awaiting a kidney transplant. That journey came full circle this holiday season when he returned to the Transplant Center at Mayo Clinic in Rochester, Minnesota&nbsp;—&nbsp;this time healthy, thriving and dressed in a familiar red suit.&nbsp;</p>



<p>"Not only are kidney transplants possible,&nbsp;they're&nbsp;doable,&nbsp;life-changing.&nbsp;And Mayo is just a phenomenal place to have it done,"&nbsp;Dan says.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>



<p>Each holiday season, Dan volunteers as Santa, spreading joy and connection within the community. This year, he wanted that tradition of giving to include the Mayo Clinic transplant team who supported him through his transplant journey.&nbsp;</p>


<div class="wp-block-image is-style-center-align-caption">
<figure class="aligncenter size-large is-resized"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="1024" src="https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2025/12/Dan-Reed-Steve-Eckhouse-1x1-1-1024x1024.jpg" alt="Steve&nbsp;Eckhouse and Dan Reed" class="wp-image-409248" style="width:436px;height:auto" srcset="https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2025/12/Dan-Reed-Steve-Eckhouse-1x1-1-1024x1024.jpg 1024w, https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2025/12/Dan-Reed-Steve-Eckhouse-1x1-1-300x300.jpg 300w, https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2025/12/Dan-Reed-Steve-Eckhouse-1x1-1-150x150.jpg 150w, https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2025/12/Dan-Reed-Steve-Eckhouse-1x1-1-768x768.jpg 768w, https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2025/12/Dan-Reed-Steve-Eckhouse-1x1-1-1536x1536.jpg 1536w, https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2025/12/Dan-Reed-Steve-Eckhouse-1x1-1-2048x2048.jpg 2048w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Steve&nbsp;Eckhouse and Dan Reed</figcaption></figure>
</div>


<p>Dan was joined by&nbsp;Steve&nbsp;Eckhouse, his best friend of more than 40 years and the person who helped&nbsp;initiate&nbsp;the living donor chain that&nbsp;ultimately led&nbsp;to Dan receiving a kidney. Together,&nbsp;they visited&nbsp;Mayo&nbsp;Clinic&nbsp;physicians, nurses, transplant&nbsp;coordinators&nbsp;and staff to personally express their gratitude.&nbsp;</p>



<p>"I was happy to learn&nbsp;that&nbsp;anybody could possibly be eligible&nbsp;(to be a donor),"&nbsp;Steve says.&nbsp;</p>


<div class="wp-block-image">
<figure class="aligncenter size-large is-resized"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="1024" src="https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2025/12/Dan-Reed-Santa-team-1x1-1-1024x1024.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-409194" style="width:440px;height:auto" srcset="https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2025/12/Dan-Reed-Santa-team-1x1-1-1024x1024.jpg 1024w, https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2025/12/Dan-Reed-Santa-team-1x1-1-300x300.jpg 300w, https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2025/12/Dan-Reed-Santa-team-1x1-1-150x150.jpg 150w, https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2025/12/Dan-Reed-Santa-team-1x1-1-768x768.jpg 768w, https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2025/12/Dan-Reed-Santa-team-1x1-1.jpg 1026w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"></figure>
</div>


<p>For the transplant team, the visit offered a meaningful opportunity to see the impact of their work&nbsp;—&nbsp;from a patient thriving after&nbsp;transplant, to the friend who helped make it possible.&nbsp;</p>



